      "comment": "KRAKEN CHIEF (1) has some solid form under his belt and proved too strong last time to win by 2 lengths at this track in a handy 28.42 beating Serrated Edge. The form out of his last race has been franked. Hard to go past. GO PIKACHU (6) held his own to the line last start and filled a minor placing, beaten only 0.8 lengths (25.49) behind Aston Cleese at Ballarat. Expected to be in the finish again. WHITE SHIRAZ (3) showed little early speed at her last couple, the latest finishing fifth (42.73) in a Grade 5 at Sandown. Has ability and is one of the better chances. LEAVE ME IN (2) can fill a top-three spot.",
